{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7yPYphRnL6JUZxpgKU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed and tests pass.\n\n**Root cause:** In `src/userService.js`, the cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it left out `includeArchived`. When some caller fetched a team *with* archived users, that list got cached under the team key. The people picker, which requests the same team with `includeArchived: false`, then received the archived-inclusive list from cache. It self-corrected after ~1 minute because that's when the 60s cache entry expired — matching the report exactly.\n\n**Fix:** The key now incorporates the flag: `users:${opts.team}:archived=${Boolean(opts.includeArchived)}`, so archived-included and archived-excluded requests occupy separate cache entries and no longer collide.\n\n`npm test` passes. Note the existing test suite only covers `cache.js`; there's no test exercising `getUsers`, so this collision wasn't caught. I can add a regression test for it if you'd like."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":295,"cache_read_input_tokens":23822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":295},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bd64e88f-11ff-45dc-96a3-e9c9af548a29","uuid":"9548c607-2023-4f1c-883e-c59d8f592153","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:47:31.408Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7yN71TcKZ7PupmUiBs"}
